Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Add AI_LABEL_MAP override, CI (tests + pip-audit), and
 model/reverse-search docs

- labels: AI_LABEL_MAP override (by index or label string) so ultra-light or
  non-standard models can be swapped in without code changes; wired through
  config -> registry -> factory/worker; unit tests added
- .github/workflows/ci.yml: run unit+integration tests (ML libs stubbed) and a
  pip-audit dependency vulnerability scan (informational)
- .env.example: document the default SigLIP2 detector, an ultra-light CPU/low-RAM
  alternative, and AI_LABEL_MAP usage
- docs/MODELS_AND_REVERSE_SEARCH.md: rationale for the AI model (CPU/low-RAM) and
  the Google Lens reverse-search method, with honest limitations

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
